<H1 class="visuallyhidden">Headlines</H1>


  
<div class="main-visual flexslider">

<ul class="slides">
		  <li aria-hidden="true"><A href='https://www.npr.org/sections/therecord/2018/03/07/591234978/you-re-not-my-first-enemy-in-long-lost-jewish-songs-of-wwii-pain-and-defiance' target='_blank'><img 
		  alt="NPR Review of Yiddish Glory" src="user_files/IMG_0505.jpg"></A><div class="flex-caption"><H2 class="flex-headline"><a href='https://www.npr.org/sections/therecord/2018/03/07/591234978/you-re-not-my-first-enemy-in-long-lost-jewish-songs-of-wwii-pain-and-defiance' >NPR Review of Yiddish Glory</a></H2><div class="flex-text">
			  <P>Anna Shternshis and Psoy Korolenko perform at UCI with a program on Yiddish songs from World War II. Hosted by the Center for Jewish Studies.</P></div></div></LI>
		  <li aria-hidden="true"><A href='http://bit.ly/2hKh8Jd' target='_blank'><img 
		  alt="UCI launches Center for Jewish Studies" src="user_files/JewishStudiesCenter-Spotlight.png"></A><div class="flex-caption"><H2 class="flex-headline"><a href='http://bit.ly/2hKh8Jd' >UCI launches Center for Jewish Studies</a></H2><div class="flex-text">
			  <P>A new Center for Jewish Studies at the University of California, Irvine will bring together faculty, students, visiting scholars and members of the public interested in exploring Judaism.</P></div></div></LI>
		  <li aria-hidden="true"><A href='http://bit.ly/UCIHumanities2017' target='_blank'><img 
		  alt="Alumna success" src="user_files/Kerner.png"></A><div class="flex-caption"><H2 class="flex-headline"><a href='http://bit.ly/UCIHumanities2017' >Alumna success</a></H2><div class="flex-text">
			  <P>Lauren Kerner '17 (B.A. History) currently serves as UC Santa Barbara's Israel Engagement Coordinator. While at UCI, her senior honors thesis centered on architectural spaces in relation to creedal diversity in Jerusalem. Her story is on pages 18-19.</P></div></div></LI>
		  <li aria-hidden="true"><img 
		  alt="Jewish Studies public lectures" src="user_files/holocaust_museum.jpg"><div class="flex-caption"><H2 class="flex-headline">Jewish Studies public lectures</H2><div class="flex-text">
			  <P>The UCI Center for Jewish Studies offers public lectures in Jewish studies, the Holocaust, and Israel, featuring renowned scholars and writers from around the world.  Photo: Holocaust lecture, in conjunction with the US Holocaust Memorial Museum.</P></div></div></LI>
		  <li aria-hidden="true"><img 
		  alt="Sephardic studies" src="user_files/shephardic.jpg"><div class="flex-caption"><H2 class="flex-headline">Sephardic studies</H2><div class="flex-text">
			  <P>The UCI Center for Jewish Studies has a strong presence in Sephardic Studies, with faculty working on Judeo-Spanish, Sephardic, and Latin American Jewish literature and history.<br />
Photo: Interior of the Magen David synagogue in Mexico City.</P></div></div></LI>
		  <li aria-hidden="true"><img 
		  alt="Classes on Zionism and Israel" src="user_files/zikhron.jpg"><div class="flex-caption"><H2 class="flex-headline">Classes on Zionism and Israel</H2><div class="flex-text">
			  <P>We offer a wide array of classes on Jewish history, religion, and culture, including regular course offerings on the history of Zionism, the State of Israel, and a popular class on the history of Jerusalem.</P></div></div></LI></ul></div>
  
